  "summary": "A rare neuroendocrine neoplasm that can develop at various body sites. When found in the adrenal gland, they are referred to as pheochromocytomas. They are rare tumors, with an overall estimated incidence of 1 in 300,000. About 75% of paragangliomas are sporadic, the remaining 25% are hereditary.",
